    <boxed-text id="box01" position="float">
      <sec id="sec20y">
        <title>Key Points</title>
        <list list-type="bullet">
          <list-item>
            <p>PEcnv is a novel approach to detect copy number variations that vary in size and copy number.</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>PEcnv enables accurate detection of copy number variants with short-to-medium length, which are hard to identify with existing approaches but have been emphasized recently in cancer research and treatment development.</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>PEcnv is among the first approaches to incorporate the genomic bases’ features around a target base to correct the bias and noise on the read depth. This solves the lack of training data for clinical panel sequencing data.</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>PEcnv applies to panel sequencing data and also works for whole genome sequencing and whole-exome sequencing data.</p>
          </list-item>
        </list>
      </sec>
    </boxed-text>
  </sec>
